  <h2>24 Hour Access Procedures</h2>
  <p>At 10:00pm Sunday night through Thursday night the doors to the library will be locked and access will only be through the east and west concourse doors using a swipe reader. You must swipe your card and enter your pin. Your pin is the month and date of your birth. Upon doing this the doors will release for approximately 8 seconds to allow access or you can press the handicap button which will allow the doors to open.</p>
  <p>At 7:00am Monday through Friday the doors will be unlocked and the swipe card reader will be disabled.</p>
  <p>The swipe card system is only set up for NDID’s. SMC, HC, and Bethel students must call 631-6350 and the security monitor will come and check ID’s and allow access.</p>
